 "benefits": [
  "Designed specifically for computer printing applications including dot matrix/impact",
  "#300 adhesive bonds well to a wide variety of substrates including metals, high surface energy (HSE) plastics and low surface energy (LSE) plastics.",
  "55# densified kraft liner assures consistent die cutting.",
  "3M™ Label Material 7883 is UL recognized (Files MH11410 and MH16411) and CSA accepted (File 99316). See the UL and CSA listings for details.",
  "The matte coating resists degradation from scuffing, chemicals, moisture, and wide temperature fluctuations.",
  "The topcoat also provides improved ink anchorage for traditional forms of press printing.",
  "It is ideal for applications requiring high initial adhesion especially to LSE plastic surfaces."
